[{"id":41849,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["$15 \\mathrm{~m}$","$20 \\sqrt{2} \\mathrm{~m}$","$5 \\mathrm{~m}$","$10 \\sqrt{2} \\mathrm{~m}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"As $\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{S}}=\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{ut}}+\\frac{1}{2} \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{a}} \\mathrm{t}^{2}$\r\n\r\n$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{S}}=(5 \\hat{i}+4 \\hat{j}) 2+\\frac{1}{2}(4 \\hat{i}+4 \\hat{j}) 4$\r\n\r\n$=10 \\hat{i}+8 \\hat{j}+8 \\hat{i}+8 \\hat{j}$\r\n\r\n$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{r}}_{\\mathrm{f}}-\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{r}}_{\\mathrm{i}}=18 \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}+16 \\hat{\\mathrm{j}}$\r\n\r\n$\\left[\\mathrm{as} \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{s}}=\\right.$ change in position $\\left.=\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{r}}_{\\mathrm{f}}-\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{r}}_{\\mathrm{i}}\\right]$\r\n\r\n$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{r}}_{\\mathrm{r}}=20 \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}+20 \\hat{\\mathrm{j}}$\r\n\r\n$\\left|\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{r}}_{\\mathrm{r}}\\right|=20 \\sqrt{2}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41775,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["$\\tan ^{-1} \\frac{(2 \\vec{Q}-2 \\vec{P})}{2 \\vec{Q}+2 \\vec{P}}$","$0^{\\circ}$","$\\tan ^{-1}(\\mathrm{P} / \\mathrm{Q})$","$\\tan ^{-1}(2 \\mathrm{Q} / \\mathrm{P})$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{R}}=(2 \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{Q}}+2 \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{P}})+(2 \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{Q}}-2 \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{P}}) \\\\\n& \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{R}}=4 \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{Q}}\n\\end{aligned}$\nAngle between $\\vec{Q}$ and $\\vec{R}$ is zero.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41802,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>GIven vector are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>-</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p>Component of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></math> along <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#183;</mo><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#183;</mo><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mrow><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><msqrt><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mfrac></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41868,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["4.4%","2.27%","1.7%","2.7%"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math> <mrow> <mtext>T</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mi>&pi;</mi> <msqrt> <mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>L</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>g</mtext> </mrow> </mfrac> </msqrt> </mrow> </math><br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mo>&there4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</mo> <msup> <mtext>T</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mo>=</mo> <mn>4</mn> <msup> <mi>&pi;</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>L</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>g</mtext> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math><br /><br /><math> <mrow><mo>&there4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</mo> <mtext>g</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mn>4</mn> <msup> <mi>&pi;</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> <mfrac> <mrow> <mtext>L</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mtext>T</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math><br /><br />% Error in g <math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mo>&Delta;</mo> <mtext>L</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>L</mtext> <mn>0</mn> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>&times;</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </mfenced> <mo>+</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mo>&Delta;</mo> <mtext>T</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>T</mtext> <mn>0</mn> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>&times;</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> </math><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>&times;</mo> <mn>1</mn> <msup> <mn>0</mn> <mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>3</mn> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>0.20</mtext> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>&times;</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </mfenced> <mo>+</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mfenced close=\"}\" open=\"{\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>9</mn> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>&times;</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mn>0</mn> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> </math><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>0.5</mtext> <mo>+</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>9</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> </math><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>0.5</mtext> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>9</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>0.5</mtext> <mo>+</mo> <mtext>2.22</mtext> </mrow> </math><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;= 2.7%","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":41791,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Using parallelogram law of vector addition, the formula can be written as</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi>net</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></msqrt></math></p><p>The data given is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mover><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mover><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Since the vectors are perpendicular&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mn>90</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">F</mi><mi>net</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41794,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a3588fa5-957c-4fc2-a4c4-8e9f56d9cf98-9895950.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 266px;\" /></p><p>Give:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>.</p><p>Displacement is defined to be the change in position of an object. As we can see from the above figure, displacement will be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41758,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["0.08","0.06","0.18","0.24"],"answer":1,"solution":"Mean $= \\frac{20.00+19.75+17.01+18.25}{4} = \\frac{75.01}{4} = 18.7525$ cm.<br>Absolute errors: $|20.00-18.7525|=1.2475$, $|19.75-18.7525|=0.9975$, $|17.01-18.7525|=1.7425$, $|18.25-18.7525|=0.5025$.<br>Mean absolute error $= \\frac{1.2475+0.9975+1.7425+0.5025}{4} = \\frac{4.49}{4} = 1.1225$.<br>Relative error $= \\frac{1.1225}{18.7525} \\approx 0.06$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41771,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/LUMgvlw_RQvl1yaAJkOmISg6fLh7OpKM5hgsTyYLa5E.original.fullsize.png\"><br />$\\begin{aligned} & \\vec{R}=\\left(A+\\frac{A}{\\sqrt{2}}\\right) \\hat{i}+\\left(A-\\frac{A}{\\sqrt{2}}\\right) \\hat{j} \\\\ & |\\vec{R}|=\\sqrt{\\left(A+\\frac{A}{\\sqrt{2}}\\right)^2+\\left(A-\\frac{A}{\\sqrt{2}}\\right)^2}=\\sqrt{3} A\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41779,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["(A)-(III), (B)-(IV), (C)-(II), (D)-(I)","(A)-(IV), (B)-(III), (C)-(I), (D)-(II)","(A)-(II), (B)-(I), (C)-(IV), (D)-(III)","(A)-(I), (B)-(II), (C)-(III), (D)-(IV)"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Rules for significant figures:</p><p>1. All non-zero numbers are significant</p><p>2. Zeros between two non-zero digits are significant</p><p>3. Leading zeros are not significant</p><p>4. Trailing zeros to the right of the decimal are significant</p><p>5. Trailing zeros in a whole number with the decimal shown are significant</p><p>6. Trailing zeros in a whole number with no decimal shown are not significant</p><p>From above rule, we get</p><p>(A)-(II), (B)-(I), (C)-(IV), (D)-(III)</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (01 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41831,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>%</mo></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>l</mi></mrow><msup><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>l</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>T</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>200</mn></mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>50</mn></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (18 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41780,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>39</mn><mo>.9</mo><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>37</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>35</mn><mo>.6</mo><mo>%</mo></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>The resistance of the wire is given as, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>ρ</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>A</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>Therefore, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ρ</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mfrac><mi>A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ρ</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>For percentage error, we can write <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>100</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.05</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.35</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.2</mo></mrow><mn>15</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>100</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>75</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>100</mn></math></p><p>Hence, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>39</mn><mo>.9</mo><mo>%</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (01 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41846,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>0.2</mtext><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>6.8</mtext><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>3.5</mtext><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>0.7</mtext><mo>%</mo></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>0.1</mn><mn>55</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>30</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mn>0.06848</mn></math><br />Percentage error <math><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>6.8</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41870,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["$1 \\%$","$2 \\%$","$6 \\%$","$3 \\%$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Given : $\\frac{\\Delta I}{I} \\times 100=2 \\%$;\n$\\frac{\\Delta R}{R} \\times 100=1 \\%$ and $\\frac{\\Delta t}{t} \\times 100=1 \\%$\nHeat produced, $H=I^2 R t$\nMaximum possible error in heat produced,\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& =\\frac{\\Delta H}{H} \\times 100 \\\\\n& =2\\left(\\frac{\\Delta I}{I} \\times 100\\right)+\\frac{\\Delta R}{R} \\times 100+\\frac{\\Delta t}{t} \\times 100 \\\\\n& =2 \\times 2 \\%+1 \\%+1 \\%=6 \\%\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (19 May Online)","image":null},{"id":41795,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given:&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>V</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>49</mn><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>V</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>49</mn><mn>50</mn></mfrac><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi></math></p><p>So least count will be</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>V</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>49</mn><mn>50</mn></mfrac><mo>&#183;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>50</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>As we know,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Applying log on both sides, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>l</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>h</mi><mo>&#8211;</mo><mi>l</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>h</mi><mo>&#8217;</mo></math></p><p>Differentiating both sides, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>&#956;</mi></mrow><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow><mi>h</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>For calculation, all errors will be added, therefore</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>&#956;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>41</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Hence,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>41</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (29 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41759,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["1.33%","1.67%","2.67%","2.33%"],"answer":1,"solution":"For parallel combination: $k_{eq} = k_1 + k_2 = 10 + 20 = 30$ N/m<br>For sum, absolute errors add:<br>$\\Delta k_{eq} = \\Delta k_1 + \\Delta k_2 = 0.2 + 0.3 = 0.5$ N/m<br>Percentage error $= \\frac{\\Delta k_{eq}}{k_{eq}} \\times 100 = \\frac{0.5}{30} \\times 100 = 1.67\\%$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (21 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41801,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>75</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Dimensional formula for Torque</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mi>&#964;</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><msup><mi>ML</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Now the percentage error in torque can be calculated by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#964;</mi><mo>%</mo><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow><mi>L</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>T</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#964;</mi><mo>%</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41856,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math><mn>2.5</mn><mi>%</mi></math>","<math><mn>1.0</mn><mi>%</mi></math>","<math><mn>2.0</mn><mi>%</mi></math>","<math><mn>0.5</mn><mi>%</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Volume,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>.</mo><mi>l</mi></math></p><p>In differential form,<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>A</mi></mrow><mi>A</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>l</mi></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>A</mi></mrow><mi>A</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>l</mi></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>A</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p></blockquote><blockquote><p>Also resistance of wire is as follows <math><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#961;</mi><mfrac><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br />diffrentiation formula for resistance is as follows</p><p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>l</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>A</mi></mrow><mi>A</mi></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>l</mi></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>l</mi></mfrac><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>l</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#183;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>l</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>%</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>%</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>%</mo></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi>%</mi></math> change in <math><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0.5</mn><mi>%</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>%</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41848,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mi>v</mi></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>v</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ufkuzwqpopglogewmlmccljrfcejmilearjzrjhbxinxshgvcl.png\" /> <br/><br/> <math><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><msup><mrow><mn>60</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>o</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math> <br/><br/> <math><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41767,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/UoIFsxsiGDsDS75OozfaQtnnhL3T_jj0yQSfAlZz_jI.original.fullsize.png\"/>\n$\\begin{aligned}&amp; \\mathrm{B} \\cos \\theta=\\frac{\\mathrm{B}}{2} \\\\\n&amp; \\Rightarrow \\theta=60^{\\circ}\\end{aligned}$\nSo, angle between $\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{A}} \\&amp; \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{B}}$ is $90^{\\circ}+60^{\\circ}=150^{\\circ}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41871,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["$6 \\%$","zero","$1 \\%$","$3 \\%$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{R}=\\frac{\\mathrm{V}}{\\mathrm{i}}$\n$\\Rightarrow \\quad\\left|\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{R}}{\\mathrm{R}}\\right|=\\left|\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{V}}{\\mathrm{V}}\\right|+\\left|\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{i}}{\\mathrm{i}}\\right|$\n$\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{V}}{\\mathrm{V}} \\times 100=3$\n$\\Rightarrow \\quad \\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{V}}{\\mathrm{V}}=0.03$\nSimilarly, $\\frac{\\Delta i}{i}=0.03$\nHence $\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{R}}{\\mathrm{R}}=0.06$\nSo percentage error is $\\frac{\\Delta \\mathrm{R}}{\\mathrm{R}} \\times 100=6 \\%$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (Offline)","image":null},{"id":41834,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>76</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>56</mn><mo>%</mo></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#937;</mi><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi></math></p><p>As volume of wire remains constant so</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p><p>Now, Resistance&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>R</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#961;</mi><mi>&#8467;</mi></mrow><mi>A</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>&#961;</mi><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#215;</mo><msub><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msubsup><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><msubsup><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5625</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#937;</mi></math></p><p>So <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp;change in resistance</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5625</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>1</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>56</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41760,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["0.1","0.8","0.7","0.6"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\text { Fractional error }=2 \\frac{\\Delta X}{X}+\\frac{3}{2} \\frac{\\Delta Y}{Y}+\\frac{2}{5} \\frac{\\Delta Z}{Z} \\\\ & =2(0.1)+\\frac{3}{2}(0.2)+\\frac{2}{5}(0.5) \\\\ & =0.2+0.3+0.2=0.7\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (8 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41860,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>α</mo></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>α</mo></math>","<math><mo>α</mo></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>α</mo></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mo>&#8756;</mo><mtext>&#8201;&#8201;</mtext><mfrac><mrow><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac><mtext>&#8201;&#8201;</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#8201;&#8201;</mtext><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mtext>&#8201;&#8201;</mtext><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#916;</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><mi>s</mi></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd/></mtr><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mo>&#945;</mo></mtd></mtr></mtable></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr)","image":null},{"id":41809,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><msup><mi>y</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup></math></p><p>Relative error is given by&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>z</mi></mrow><mi>z</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mi>y</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Now, maximum percentage error in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>z</mi></mrow><mi>z</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mn>4</mn></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>%</mo></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41785,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>%</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given that, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>V</mi><mi>I</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>According to error analysis</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>I</mi></mrow><mi>I</mi></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>200</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>200</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Thus, the percentage error can be calculated as follows:<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>%</mo><mo> </mo><mtext>error</mtext><mo> </mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>100</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>200</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>100</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (29 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41793,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The given data is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>l</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mi>A</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>96</mn><mi>A</mi></math></p><p>Using the formula&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#961;</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>A</mi></mfrac></math>,&nbsp;the new&nbsp;resistance is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>R</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#961;</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>96</mn><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>R</mi><mo>'</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mi>R</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mi>R</mi></math></p><p>Hence, the percentage increase is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (06 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41781,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>−</mo><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi>R</mi><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>−</mo><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>The magnitude of resultant vector <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math> is given by, </p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>B</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>θ</mi></msqrt></math></p><p>Here <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi></math></p><p>Then <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>cos</mi><mi>θ</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mi>θ</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi>R</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfrac><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41805,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>42</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>47</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>19</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/63bb7d82cb755babaefa1a6c.jpg\" style=\"width: 120px; height: 109px;\" /></p><p>The distance travelled by the person&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;will be equal to the arch length.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>60</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>80</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p>Now the magnitude of displacement can be found using subtraction of vectors. Therefore,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mi>s</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mi>s</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>135</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>80</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>47</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41814,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["Both Statement I and Statement II are true.","Statement I&nbsp;is true but Statement II&nbsp;is false.","Both Statement I and Statement II are false.","Statement I is false but Statement II is true."],"answer":0,"solution":"Use triangle law of vector addition,&nbsp;<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bce097f1-d91d-4d8d-99aa-44d92ad8b5b3-image.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 188px;\" /><br />here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, since net force is zero it means the body is in equilibrium so both the statements are correct.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41813,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Mathematics in Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>155</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0083</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>083</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0155</mn></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>g</mi><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>bd</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#948;</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><mi>Y</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>l</mi></mrow><mn>1</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mi>b</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>&#948;</mi></mrow><mi>&#948;</mi></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><mi>Y</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0005</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>001</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0025</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0025</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>002</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0155</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (01 Sep Shift 2)","image":null}]